column5: just wondering if anyone could let me know if there is any ice forming along hwy 35.  any help would be greatly appreciated. Cheers Jeff
Nah, I think they still use salt on the roads there, helps keep ice from forming on the highways.

yes last week some of the smaller ponds and small lakes in haliburton had ice on them,but then the rain came,...so not much going on yest,they are ready to freeze we just need a few cold days without any rain !!!they will skim over this weekend probly,the smaller ones i mean....
Thanks I'm hoping to hit cedar(sludge lake next sat morning. Usually has a few inches of ice by now.
I was up there last weekend, I'm pretty sure Sludge won't be safe this weekend
All the MODIS pics from the last little while are so cloudy!
I bet it's starting now.  Was out on Quinte Tu/Wed with YoungOne and Kevin - overnight ice was forming in various areas...
